PART 2 — CIRCUIT BREAKERS (hard limits, non-negotiable)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

These limits are compiled into the Rust binary. They cannot be overridden
at runtime without a full redeploy. This is intentional.

┌──────────────────────────────────┬──────────────┬──────────────────────────┐
│ PARAMETER                        │ LIMIT        │ ACTION ON BREACH         │
├──────────────────────────────────┼──────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│ Max single order size            │ $1,000 USDC  │ Silently reduce to $1,000│
│ Max concurrent open orders       │ 10           │ Refuse new orders        │
│ Max orders per second            │ 3            │ Queue with backpressure  │
│ Max outstanding NAV exposure     │ 5% of NAV    │ Cancel all → disconnect  │
│ Daily loss limit                 │ 2% of NAV    │ Kill switch, alert Slack │
│ Single market exposure           │ 1% of NAV    │ Block further orders     │
│ Price drift abort (3-sec window) │ 1.5% move    │ Cancel pending order     │
│ Engine offline threshold         │ 30 seconds   │ Alert + auto-reconnect   │
└──────────────────────────────────┴──────────────┴──────────────────────────┘

Circuit breaker implementation sketch:

use std::sync::atomic::{AtomicBool, AtomicI64, Ordering};

static KILL_SWITCH:   AtomicBool = AtomicBool::new(false);
static DAILY_PNL:     AtomicI64  = AtomicI64::new(0);   // in USDC cents
static OPEN_EXPOSURE: AtomicI64  = AtomicI64::new(0);   // in USDC cents

const MAX_DAILY_LOSS_CENTS: i64 = 200_000;   // -$2,000
const MAX_EXPOSURE_CENTS: i64   = 5_000_000; // $50,000 (5% of $1M NAV)

fn check_circuit_breakers() -> Result<(), &'static str> {
    if KILL_SWITCH.load(Ordering::Relaxed) {
        return Err("kill switch active");
    }
    if DAILY_PNL.load(Ordering::Relaxed) < -MAX_DAILY_LOSS_CENTS {
        KILL_SWITCH.store(true, Ordering::SeqCst);
        return Err("daily loss limit breached");
    }
    if OPEN_EXPOSURE.load(Ordering::Relaxed) > MAX_EXPOSURE_CENTS {
        return Err("exposure limit breached");
    }
    Ok(())
}

