PART 4 — 3-SECOND IN-PLAY FAILSAFE (DETAILED)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

This is Sentinel's primary real-time protection mechanism.

Timeline of a sports order:
  T+0ms:    RN1 places order, we detect it
  T+5ms:    Our order submitted to CLOB
  T+5ms:    CLOB enters 3-second delay queue (in-play game)
  T+3005ms: CLOB attempts to match our order
  ← Between T+5ms and T+3005ms, our failsafe is active

Failsafe logic (must be EXTREMELY reliable):
  - Poll GET /price every 100ms (30 polls in 3 seconds)
  - Calculate: |current_price - entry_price| / entry_price > 0.015
  - On breach: fire DELETE /order/{id} immediately
  - Confirm cancellation: poll GET /order/{id} until status = "cancelled"
  - If cancellation fails (network error): retry 3 times with 50ms backoff
  - If still fails after retries: trigger full kill switch (nuclear option)

Market scenarios requiring abort:
  - Goal scored in a soccer match (odds swing 20-40% instantly)
  - Game-ending point in CS:GO (100% move)
  - Injury/disqualification during match
  - Any Δprice > 1.5% in the 3-second window

Pre-game order wipe handler:
  The CLOB cancels all orders at game start. But the engine must also:
  1. Listen for game_start_at timestamp from Gamma API event data
  2. Set a timer: cancel own orders 10 seconds BEFORE game_start_at
  3. At game_start_at: flush entire order cache, assume all are cancelled
  4. Enter "in-play mode": enable 3-second failsafe for all new orders

