PART 5 — FORMAL VERIFICATION (Foundry + Halmos)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Any Solidity interaction (approvals, direct contract calls) must be
formally verified before deploying to mainnet.

Tools:
  Foundry Forge:  Fuzz testing with random inputs (unit-level)
  Halmos:         Symbolic execution — mathematically proves invariants
  Certora Prover: Enterprise-grade formal verification (optional)

Critical invariants to prove:
  1. approve() can never be called for more than MAX_ALLOWANCE
  2. cancel_order() always succeeds if order is in pending state
  3. The kill switch, once activated, cannot be deactivated by a single call
  4. Daily loss calculation can never be negative (underflow)

Foundry invariant test example:
